<recipe>
<title>
Peach Syrup
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
</details>
<ingredients>
6 very ripe peaches sliced
1/2-3/4 c . granulated sugar
1/2 lemon juiced
2 T . water
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Place peach slices in a sauce pot.
Add sugar, lemon juice, and water to peach slices. Stir to combine.
Cook over medium-low heat for about 45-60 minutes, or until peach slices have given off a lot of juice and have cooked down.
Once slices have cooked down, you can puree it or leave the syrup chunky.
</instructions>
</recipe>
